  "title": "A Lesbian in a Bear Store",
  "description": "Professional lesbian Willow Rosenberg and her mum’s extensive Beanie Baby collection will take you on a journey of love, loss, lesbians, discovery, 2010s Tumblr, 2020s TikTok, bad(ish) poetry, and cats. Don’t miss this Jenny Award nominated show that audiences called “funny, relatable, and occasionally heartbreaking”!",
  "credits": "<strong>Playwright</strong>: Willow Rosenberg<br/><strong>Director</strong>: Hayden Maines<br/><strong>Cast</strong>: Willow Rosenberg, Willow's Mum's Beanie Baby Collection<br/>",
  "website": "https://find.willowrosenberg.space",
  "plain_language": "A Lesbian in a Bear Store is a one-person show where Willow Rosenberg shares stories from her life through short scenes, poems, and fun characters, including her mum’s Beanie Babies. Some stories are funny, some sad, and some imagined. Willow explores her queer identity, chronic illness, coming out, and loss, while also finding love and community along the way.",
